  "text": "We showed that mean AST, ALT, and TB concentrations dropped at 14 days after shunt treatment, and ascites and variceal bleeding disappeared. This showed that IVC stenting combined with DIPS could have a good clinical effect for patients with SOS associated with botanical hepatotoxicity, which confirms the results of some previous studies of TIPS [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In the present study, the levels of AST and ALT were higher than for other causes of liver cirrhosis, but TB was not 7 higher. The cause of this phenomenon warrants further study. In our study, HE was still a problem despite its low incidence compared with other diseases that TIPS cannot completely cure [CITATION_3] .",
